The paper deals with interference modelling in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of stochastic geometry models and performance evaluation also suggests the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions Low-Power Wide-Area Networks (LPWANs), which are a type of wireless communication technology, indicating the Mobile Computing (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of two LPWA technologies, which could fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
